==Tatar==
===Etymology===
Akin to Old English ''curd, crud'', German ''gort milch'' - fermented milk; from ''gären'' - to ferment. 

#''Phonetic Roman spelling:'' '''curd.'''
#''Phonetic Cyrillic spelling:'' '''курд''' ''(See Ref.)''.
===Noun===

'''curd'''
#[[curd#English|curd]]. The part of [[milk]] that [[coagulate]]. Cottage cheese. 
# Small dryed curd balls used as snack.


